            <div class="info">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="sub-title">List of Jobs (GET Request)</p>
                        <div class="info">
                            <p>
                                Click on <code>Jobs</code> in the navigation bar. This will take you to the list of
                                jobs. There are two buttons available for each job. One to Edit the job and another to
                                Delete the job.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
    
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="sub-title">Add a New Job (POST Request)</p>
                        <div class="info">
                            <p>
                                Click on <code>Add Job</code> in the navigation bar. It will redirect to new page that contains
                                a form with three fields. <code>Job Name</code>, <code>Part Id</code>, and <code>Quantity</code>.
                                Job Name and Part Id must be unique and all three forms are required.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Clicking on <code>Add</code> will add the job in the database and redirect you to job list page.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
    
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p class="sub-title">Edit a Job (PUT Request)</p>
                        <div class="info">
                            <p>
                                Click on <code>Jobs</code> in the navigation bar. It will display list of 
                                jobs in the database. There is an <code>Edit</code> button for each job.
                                Clicking on the button will open a new page that contains the form similar 
                                to adding a job. <code>Job Name</code> and <code>Part Id</code> are not allowed to change
                                as they represent uniqueness of a job. Clicking on updaet button will take back to 
                                list of jobs where you can see the changes reflected.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
    
                <div class="card">
